The **Provider Data Catalog API** provides access to official CMS data used on the **Medicare Care Compare** website and directories.

   * [Home](https://data.cms.gov/provider-data/)
   * [About](https://data.cms.gov/provider-data/about)

### Catalog

A comprehensive list of all datasets available from the `metastore/schemas` endpoint:

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
provider_data() |>
  reframe(
    id = row_number(),
    title,
    description,
    dates = issued,
    released,
    links = distribution_downloadURL,
    website = landingPage) |>
  arrange(id, title) |>
  gt() |>
  cols_width(
    id ~ px(40),
    description ~ px(225)
    ) |> 
  tab_header(title = md("**Provider Data Catalog API**: Datasets Available")) |> 
  opt_all_caps() |>
  opt_table_font(font = google_font(name = "Rubik")) |>
  fmt_date(columns = c(dates, released)) |>
  fmt_url(
    columns = links,
    show_underline = TRUE,
    label = "Download [.csv]") |>
  fmt_url(
    columns = website,
    show_underline = TRUE,
    label = "Landing Page") |>
  tab_style(
    style = css(
      position = "sticky",
      top = "-1em",
      `z-index` = 10), 
    locations = cells_column_labels()) |>
  tab_style(
    style = cell_text(weight = "lighter", size = "small"),
    locations = cells_body(columns = c(description, dates, released))) |>
  tab_style(
    style = cell_text(
      weight = "bold",
      size = "small",
      font = google_font(name = "Fira Code")),
    locations = cells_body(columns = c(links, website))) |>
  tab_style(style     = cell_text(weight = "bold", size = "small"),
            locations = cells_body(columns = title)) |>
  cols_merge(columns = c(dates, released), pattern = "<b>ISSUED</b>: {1} <br> <b>RELEASED</b>: {2}") |>
  cols_merge(columns = c(links, website), pattern = "{1} <br> {2}") |>
  tab_options(
    column_labels.border.bottom.style = "hidden",
    column_labels.padding.horizontal = px(20),
    column_labels.background.color = "#555555",
    container.height = px(700),
    heading.align = "left",
    heading.border.bottom.color = "#555555",
    heading.title.font.weight = "bold",
    heading.background.color = "gray60",
    quarto.disable_processing = TRUE,
    table.border.top.color = "#555555",
    table.border.top.style = "hidden",
    table.width = pct(100)
  )
```

